{"id": "507", "instruction": "We now define an algorithm: The definition of a(n) is the sequence of integers representing the first column of the spectral array W(sqrt(2)), which arises in the study of the spectral properties of recurrent sequences connected to quadratic irrationalities. Given the input x_list (a series of values): [57, 58, 59, 60, 61, 62, 63, 64, 65, 66], determine the corresponding output sequence y_list.\n\nOptions:\nA. [113, 115, 117, 118, 121, 123, 125, 127, 128, 131]\nB. [322, 324, 326, 329, 331, 333, 336, 338, 341, 343]\nC. [1046, 1048, 1050, 1053, 1055, 1057, 1060, 1062, 1065, 1067]\nD. [941, 943, 945, 948, 950, 952, 955, 957, 960, 962]\nE. [528, 530, 532, 535, 537, 539, 542, 544, 547, 549]\nF. [839, 841, 843, 846, 848, 850, 853, 855, 858, 860]\nG. [424, 426, 428, 431, 433, 435, 438, 440, 443, 445]\nH. [736, 738, 740, 743, 745, 747, 750, 752, 755, 757]\nI. [216, 218, 220, 223, 225, 227, 230, 232, 235, 237]\nJ. [632, 634, 636, 639, 641, 643, 646, 648, 651, 653]", "output": "A"}
